	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />*gives you a beer*
<br />
<br />Anyway, since it seems like you're triggering this through read/writes... just be sure to designate an unused area so it doesn't conflict with mapper register writes or NES system registers.  Unfortunately, mappers are known to occupy most of the available space (N106 takes all of $4800-FFFF)
<br />
<br />I think your best best would be around $46xx... I don't think anything uses that area, and it doesn't mirror to anything either.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
