		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sounds like it'd work fine, one way would be with a cart like Squeedo that has a serial port you could send init/play signals to the PC and have the actual PC do the sound stuff there.  I thought about that before.  It would possibly work with a controller port to RS232 adapter also, but controller reads can mess it up (from toggling the strobe output shared by both ports).
<br />
<br />If you want the sound coming out of the actual NES, then of course that's something else (and the system would need to be modified).  I'm not sure what you have in mind as far as what hardware would generate the sound.

		

